<headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 19 at 10:28PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...BURSTS OF HEAVY SNOW CONTINUE FOR WASHTENAW...WAYNE...LENAWEE...AND
MONROE COUNTIES THROUGH MIDNIGHT...
WEATHER...
* Snow showers will be concentrated along the I-94 corridor
initially and then shift more into Lenawee and Monroe counties
toward midnight.
* Snow accumulations around 1 inch, with localized 2 inch totals,
are expected between 1030 PM and 1 AM after which activity
moves into Ohio.
IMPACTS...
* Rapid reduction of visibility to near a quarter mile in spots
with rapid fluctuations.
* Untreated roads remain or quickly become snow covered,
particularly on bridges, exit ramps and overpasses.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Motorists are urged to use caution and account for the variable
driving conditions by slowing down and allowing extra time.
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
